    {
      "start_time": 1108,
      "end_time": 1140,
      "annotation": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The dance of bomba was born in the 17th century and, by the 18th, it had already spread throughout the coastal regions of our island. It is a blend of three cultures: Taíno, Spanish, and African. Its dance is a challenge between the dancer and the drummer. Don Rafael Cepeda, tireless folklorist and dancer, presents these foundations to us, grounded in a dynamic truth: our native music, Puerto Rican bomba!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "tags": [
